[2026-07-17T22:30:56.914Z] vision brief (formed by the CEO):
WHAT: A browser-based personal finance dashboard web application that enables users to record financial transactions, view monthly spending summaries via charts, and manage per-category budgets with real-time tracking against actuals. The app is self-contained (client-server architecture) with local-first data persistence for privacy.

TONE & SCOPE: Modern, minimalist, and trustworthy — prioritizing clarity and ease of use over flashy features. 

IN SCOPE: 
- Transaction logging (amount, date, category, description)
- Computed monthly summaries aggregating by category and total
- Interactive charts/visualizations for spending trends
- Filterable transaction list (date range, category filters)
- Per-category budget setting with limit tracking
- Budget progress indicators (percent used vs. allowed)

OUT OF SCOPE: 
- Bank account aggregation/API integration
- Investment or savings tracking
- Tax planning tools
- Multi-user collaboration features
- Mobile app wrapper
- Cloud-based data backup

DELIVERABLES — What "done" looks like:
1) Backend/data module: RESTful endpoints (or internal service) for CRUD on transactions and budgets, monthly summary aggregation logic, data persistence layer with local storage or embedded database.
2) Frontend dashboard: Main landing page with navigation between modules; spending charts (pie/bar line); filterable transaction list with sorting/export.
3) Budgets module: Interface to create/edit/delete category budgets with limits; visual indicators showing budget health (e.g., circular progress, color-coded status).
4) Authentication or session handling (browser-based, no external auth required).
5) Data migration/reset functionality for users.

Success criteria: A user can log a transaction within 10 seconds, view monthly spending breakdown via chart with <2 second load time, set up 5 budget categories and see live alerts when approaching limits, and export the full transaction history as CSV.
